rn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uyl1665702911413.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uyl1665702911413.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uyl1665702911413.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uyl1665702911413\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Maximum Number of Locked Entities\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The maximum number of files or tables which can be open at one time depends on the number of I/O channels the DBMS connector requires and the setting for <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$MAXFILES</span> in an assignment file. Under almost all circumstances, you do not need to be concerned with this restriction because Uniface ensures that files are closed and opened as necessary. However, because a locked file cannot be closed, this maximum does determine how many files can be locked at the same time.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyl1665702911413__p_d44012e1_d44013e1_d44014e1\">The formula to determine the maximum number of simultaneously locked files is as follows:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyl1665702911413__p_d44015e1_d44016e1_d44017e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">($MAXFILES - 5)</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">/ I/O_ChannelsNeeded</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyl1665702911413__p_d44018e1_d44019e1_d44020e1\">That is, subtract five from <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$MAX_FILES</span> and divide it by the number of I/O channels required.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dfz1665702722547.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$MAX_FILES</a><p>Assign the maximum number of simultaneously open files.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Maximum Number of Locked Entities Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Maximum Number of Locked Entities The maximum number of files or tables which can be open at one time depends on the number of I/O channels the DBMS connector requires and the setting for $MAXFILES in an assignment file. Under almost all circumstances, you do not need to be concerned with this restriction because Uniface ensures that files are closed and opened as necessary. However, because a locked file cannot be closed, this maximum does determine how many files can be locked at the same time. The formula to determine the maximum number of simultaneously locked files is as follows: ($MAXFILES - 5) / I/O_ChannelsNeeded That is, subtract five from $MAX_FILES and divide it by the number of I/O channels required. Related Links $MAX_FILES Assign the maximum number of simultaneously open files. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}